The DRC has the highest rate of internal displacement globally, at 5 500 people a day. The AU must resume its leadership role; taking a back seat to SADC is a recipe for inaction. By Stephanie Wolters for ISS TODAY.   Stephanie Wolters is Head, Peace and Security Research Programme, ISS.   Photo: Moussa Faki Mahamat, Chairperson of the African Union Commission, speaks during a media conference after the summit with African leaders from the underfunded G5 Sahel anti-terror coalition in La Celle Saint Cloud, near Paris, France, 13 December 2017. EPA-EFE/CHRISTOPHE PETIT TESSON    
